def: One who encourages, incites, or helps forward; a favorer.The pope is . . . a great encourager of arts. Addison.
Sorrow; anguish of mind; mental pang. Shak.

Of or pertaining to Yezdegerd, the last Sassanian monarch ofPersia, who was overthrown by the Mohammedans; as, the Yezdegerdianera, which began on the 16th of June, a. d. 632. The era is stillused by the Parsees.
One of the grand divisions of the animal kingdom. By manywriters it was formerly included in the Radiata. [Written alsoEchinoderma.]
Earth flax, or mountain flax; a soft silky variety of asbestus.
